I'll err on the side of convenience (at …&lt;/p&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Noah Hoffman</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 06 Feb 2015 00:00:00 -0800</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:nhoffman.github.io,2015-02-06:/borborygmi/virtualbox-setup.html</guid><category>notes</category><category>linux</category><category>mac</category><category>virtualbox</category></item><item><title>Hold the pie</title><link>https://nhoffman.github.io/borborygmi/hold-the-pie.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;
I came across this visualization&lt;sup&gt;&lt;a id="fnr.1" class="footref" href="#fn.1"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; of a very simple data set, and
